title: Frieze, 1905–15
description: Alternating large and small medallions with yellow rose insets, connected by yellow rose swags. Above the smaller medallions are floral scrolls. Top has metallic gold and slight beading, scrolls, and floral swag. Bottom has stripes, beading and scrolls. Background of medallion has horizontal and vertical brown stripes. Ground fades from a brown-green to a beige (bottom to top). Printed in greens, browns, and creams, and metallic gold.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-552.
